  "label": "The Null Cantina",
  "description": "The Null Cantina occupies a recessed volume off the Anchorage’s axial spine, its walls formed from glass-dark composite scored with the port’s repeating cell-grids. Radiant filaments run through the ceiling in taut, rectilinear courses, casting hard-edged light that breaks the room into measured intervals. The bar front is faced in matte latticework that dampens glare, while sound-baffling panels leave conversation to carry in narrow, controlled bands. A ring of mooring-view apertures frames the void-channels beyond, their geometry turning the Cosmos into a disciplined, ever-present mural.",
